comments: Davis (LAL) briefly grasps Harrell's (LAC) arm off ball in the post but the contact is marginal.
Williams (LAC) leans slightly forward and initiates some contact to James' (LAL) body during the pick. The marginal contact does not affect James' ability to defend.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) briefly places a forearm on Leonard's (LAC) front during the drive. Caldwell-Pope immediately removes his forearm and the contact is deemed marginal.

After absorbing the contact to his front, Leonard (LAC) slightly extends his forearm into Caldwell-Pope's (LAL) side as both players move in the same direction during the drive. Caldwell-Pope's momentum carries him away from the marginal contact.
Kuzma (LAL) gives Leonard (LAC) room to land on the jump shot attempt. The contact to Leonard's body after he lands is deemed incidental.
Rondo (LAL) briefly places two hands on Harrell's (LAC) back during the rebound but Harrell jumps away from the marginal contact.
James (LAL) slightly extends his forearm into Leonard's (LAC) front as he changes directions during the drive. Leonard's momentum carries him away from the contact.

After absorbing the contact from James (LAL) during the drive, Leonard (LAC) reaches in and his hand lightly brushes across James' arm. The marginal contact does not affect his ability to make the pass.

Rondo (LAL) initiates some contact to Williams' (LAC) body as both players arrive at the ball simultaneously during the rebound. The contact is deemed marginal and Williams' reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
Kuzma (LAL) briefly grasps Beverley's (LAC) jersey during the rebound. He immediately removes his hand and the contact does not affect Beverley's ability to get to the rebound.
Leonard (LAC) and Kuzma (LAL) briefly engage and disengage during the rebound.
Leonard (LAC) reaches across James' (LAL) body and makes contact to his front after he has gathered the ball.
Caruso (LAL) and Beverley (LAC) briefly engage and disengage during the rebound.
Leonard (LAC) briefly places a hand on the opposite side of Davis' (LAL) body and then he immediately removes that hand. Davis' (LAL) reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
Beverley (LAC) briefly places two hands on James' (LAL) body as he pivots and the marginal contact does not affect his ability to move freely.
Beverley (LAC) makes contact with the ball during James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor is overturned to Clippers' possession.  The ball is deflected by Beverley (LAC) and re-touched by James (LAL) prior to going out bounds, causing the call on the floor to be overturned.
Davis (LAL) commits a take foul on George (LAC).
Beverley (LAC) reaches out and makes some contact to Davis' (LAL) body but he immediately removes his hand prior to Davis' upward shooting motion during his jump shot attempt.
